%I A377538 #15 Jul 08 2026 15:58:26
%S A377538 4,352,127664128,2417527943006041095012352,
%T A377538 14134776518192715599779688893236394776280723436328168813286449610340958208
%N A377538 Number of edge cuts in the n-Dorogovtsev-Goltsev-Mendes graph.
%C A377538 Using the indexing convention that DGM(0) = P_2.
%C A377538 Term a(6) has 220 decimal digits and a(7) has 659 decimal digits. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 08 2026
%H A377538 Andrew Howroyd, <a href="/A377538/b377538.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..7</a>
%H A377538 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Dorogovtsev-Goltsev-MendesGraph.html">Dorogovtsev-Goltsev-Mendes Graph</a>.
%H A377538 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/EdgeCut.html">Edge Cut</a>.
%F A377538 a(n) = 2^(3^n) - c(n) where b(n) = 2*b(n-1)^2*c(n-1), c(n) = c(n-1)^2*(3*b(n-1) + c(n-1)), with b(0) = c(0) = 1. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 08 2026
%o A377538 (PARI) a(n) = { my(b=1,c=1); for(n=1, n, my(t=2*b^2*c); c = c^3 + 3*b*c^2; b=t); 2^(3^n) - c } \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 08 2026
%K A377538 nonn
%O A377538 1,1
%A A377538 _Eric W. Weisstein_, Oct 31 2024
%E A377538 a(4) onward from _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 08 2026
